{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> πενία</b>, <br /> <i>Ionic dialect</i> -ιη, ἡ, (πένομαι) <b>poverty, need</b>, πενίῃ εἴκων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 14.157 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; οὐλομένην π. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 717; στάσις πενίας δότειρα 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “Fragmenta.” 109.5; τῇ Ἑλλάδι π. σύντροφός ἐστι,.. [ἀρετῇ] δὲ διαχρεωμένη τὴν πενίην ἀπαμύνεται 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.102; τῆς πτωχείας πενίαν φαμὲν εἶναι ἀδελφήν 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 549 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; π. δὲ σοφίαν ἔλαχε διὰ τὸ συγγενές (variant{δυστυχές}) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Fragmenta” 641 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐν πενίᾳ εἶναι, γίγνεσθαι, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Apologia” 23c, “R.” 613a; εἰς π. πολλὴν καὶ ἀπορίαν καταστῆναι 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 1.144: _plural_ πενίαι 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 8.128, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Protagoras” 353d, “R.” 618a, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>lack, need</b>, τινος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD: Plotinus Philosophus 2.4.16. \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> Πενία personified, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Poverty”, 7th-6th c.BC: Alcaeus Lyricus 92, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Symposium” 203b. \">Refs 7th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G8693","accentedUnicode":"πενία","shortDef":"poverty","mediumDef":"poverty","stepGloss":"poverty","stepTransliteration":"penia","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}